. GPTI84 Axe native app notes
.
. Transfer-ready source:
.   programs/axe_gpti84/AXGPTI84.basic
. Transfer-ready file:
.   programs/axe_gpti84/AXGPTI84.8xp
.
. Current GUI-only prototype:
.   - native graph-buffer rendering with Fix 5, ClrDraw, Line(, Text(,
.     and DispGraph
.   - no Pico or link-port traffic in this cut
.   - HOME, CHAT, and PROMPT screens
.   - HOME renders a generated app-like list directly
.   - CHAT draws from a 26x8 row buffer matching the visible graph text
.     capacity in Wabbitemu
.   - 20 generated mock chats named CHAT001, CHAT002, ...
.   - NEW CHAT opens PROMPT first; sending inserts a generated NEWxxx chat
.     at the top of the catalog and opens it with the prompt visible
.   - chat headers put title on the left and 0001/0101 in the final 9 chars,
.     with no dash separator
.   - CHAT003 is a 101-page Shakespeare-text scroll test
.   - deterministic redraw then key-wait loop:
.     down=getKey(1), up=getKey(4), left=getKey(2), right=getKey(3)
.   - generated local placeholder rows only for emulator UX testing
.   - sent prompt choices are rendered into the chat body
.   - full dynamic wrapping is intentionally not compiled into Axe; Pico/phone
.     will provide already-wrapped rows
.   - left exits only from HOME
.
. Intended next cut:
.   - replace the local row-generation routines with Pico-provided rows
.   - restore raw framed LIST, OPEN:<slot>, NEW, UP, DOWN, and
.     SEND:ACTIVE:<prompt> requests
.   - draw rows supplied by the Pico mock as pages:N 16x8 payloads
.
. The GUI prototype keeps all labels uppercase because the transfer-ready
. tokenizer and current display path only cover the stable TI-safe subset.
